comment: Use NaturalOrder comparator instead of Alphanum.
Add support for Calendar. Fix NPE in Application.getEntitiy().
Don't hold on to passed context. Use application context.
Throw exception if Application doesn't extend com.activeandroid.Application.
Don't initialize class when getting class names.
Add Update syntax. Fix migration bug.
Small optimizations. Migrations on create. Attached db.
Allow passing in integers as limit/offset.
More refactoring for speed an organization.
Removing README in hopes this fixes the borked markdown.
Move android jar to libs folder.
Fix method names. Cast instead of returning new list.
Make class again so we can check existence of subclasses.

Fix scan to work with Android first then Robolectric.
Properly implement non query sql execution.
Add links to new documentation content. Add header.
Add donate button (let's try this again...).
Make processCursor public to aid ContentProvider results.
Call ActiveAndroid.dispose() on application termination (for testing)
Fixed Set with no WHERE clause
Added Android test project with unit tests for query classes
Set PRAGMA foreign_keys=ON on every open
Format police. getItemId() fails silently. setData conforms to Android standard.
Fix scripting bug. Normalize some methods.
Switch to LruCache for entity cache.
Add overload initialize methods. Remove unnecessary synchronize modifiers.
Remove unused arg from loadFromCursor signature.

Format police. Make code more readable.

Typesafe equals, null-aware equals, implemented hashcode.
When not in db (id null), Model instance is equal only to itself.

Fix bug introduced from previous commit

My compiler was not able to deal these casts by itself.
Throw a runtime exception instead of silently failing when the framework encounters a model with no default constructor.
Made Column name optional. If not explicitly defined in the annotation, it defaults to the name of the corresponding field in the Model.
Return the row Id of the newly inserted row from Model.save
Avoid creating tables for abstract subclasses of Model
Use TextUtils.isEmpty() instead of String.isEmpty() as the latter is only available in API > 8
Add method in Table annotation for set column Id name. This fixes Issue #83
skip blank lines instead of throwing an exception

Merge branch 'fix_test' of github.com:rejasupotaro/ActiveAndroid into rejasupotaro-fix_test
Add method in Table annotation for set column Id name. This fixes Issue #83
Fixes issue from Pull Request #175 with custom Id column name.

Split sql-scripts on ";" and return a list of commands
Fix test suite by setting a different database name for CacheTest.
Add test for default column names.
Create failing test case for boolean field for Issue #203.
Handle boolean types in where arguments.
Allow Travis to build ActiveAndroid successfully. Update android-maven-plugin to 3.8.2, and download build tools in addition to the SDK.

Added a new SQL parser. This parser supports both SQL style line comments and comment blocks. SQL statements can span multiple lines but must be delimited with a semicolon. This allows for improved readability of SQL scripts.
Added several test cases for count and exists.
Trim Strings to make results more predictable while testing.
Added multiple tests for the new parser.
Configuration should return legacy parser by default.
Added a simple migration test with the default configuration.
Added additional tests for the parser, also test that semicolons inside strings and comments are ignored.
Must honor group by, having, limit and offset for exists.
Added additional tests for count and exists.

Fix the issue #106 (https://github.com/pardom/ActiveAndroid/issues/106) When use the cursor method getColumnIndex(String columnName) and have multiple columns with same name, the android implementation not return the first index, so the model entity is filled with wrong data. Create a custom search of index and replace the usages. Also add a junit test to check the issue and the fix.
